1. (a) You are not obligated to disclose or utilize, for your benefit or that of another party, any Confidential Information you obtain during your employment with the Company. However, this obligation does not apply when such disclosure is compelled by a court order, regulatory mandate, or if the information becomes publicly available, except through actions or negligence on your part;

2. (b) You shall refrain from copying, reproducing in any form, or allowing others to access copies of Documents containing Confidential Information during your employment with the Company. This includes but is not limited to letters, facsimiles, memoranda, disks, memory devices, notebooks, tapes, and other medium whether eye-readable or not;

3. (c) You are prohibited from removing or transmitting any Documents containing Confidential Information from the Company's premises or those of any affiliate during your employment, except as authorized by the Company.
